2016-01-20 : Update Joomla for compatibility with 3.7

2014-01-16 : Switch to Pydio

Rechecked that the plugins were working on all recent versions of WP, Joomla! and Drupal.
Massively update the How-To's to reflect the name change but also the fact that the conf is no more in a bootstrap file but through the Settings panel.

2013-05-10 : Update of Joomla plugin

The Joomla! plugin should be working on 2.5 (use the 1.7/ folder content) and 3.0 (new 3.0/ folder).

2011-12-16 : This is the Ajaxplorer v4 Compatible CMS Bridges Package.

The main changes are the How-To updates to be compatible with v4, and the support of Drupal 7.X
Please refer to ajaxplorer.info for more info.

Package content : 

> Modules for Drupal 6.X & 7.X
> Wordpress Extension
> Joomla Plugin for 1.5 & 1.6 , working ok on 1.7, 2.5, 3.0
> "No_Cms" : login page sample if you want a simple external login page.